						<summary>

						<p>On a fragment of a slab built into the west wall of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the Kumārasvāmin temple.</p>						

						<p>981 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 903, Vṛisha, Chaitra, śu. 5, Thursday, Pushya nakshatram and Bālava karaṇa. If the <hi rend="italic">tithi</hi> śu. 5 is a mistake for śu. 9, the details correspond to 9�1 A.D., March 17.</p>						

						<p>The record seems to register some gift of land for the repairs and whitewash to a temple (name lost). It is badly damaged.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
